agicon|SCO}} Freed\n| 30 Apr 1948\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Reserve team==\nDumbarton entered the Scottish Second XI Cup but lost in the first round to Ayr United.\n\n==Trivia==\n* The number of goals conceded in all games during the season was 111, the 12th time the unwanted 'century' had been broken.\n\n==See also==\n* [[1947\u201348 in Scottish football]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=5853 Finlayson (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=377 Jim Hoey (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=601 Alex Kay (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=5852 Jimmy Michie (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=522 Ian Hepburn (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=597 John Kelly (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=614 Gordon McFarlane (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=5854 Bobby Caldwell (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=590 Hugh Docherty (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=606 Peter Grant (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=595 Eddie McCreadie (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=603 Neil McLean (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=604 John McLennan (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=584 Dave Morrison (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=594 Jimmy Shields (Dumbarton Football Club Historical Archive)]\n*[http://sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=598 E