8 Scottish Football League}}\nA poor start, which saw only one point taken from the first 5 league games, meant that any hopes of challenging for promotion were quickly dashed and eventually Dumbarton finished 11th out of 16 with 25 points - 28 behind champions East Fife.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =L\n|date =13 August 1947\n|round =[[1947-48 Scottish Football League|Division B]]\n|score = 2\u20131\n|team1 =[[Raith Rovers F.C.|Raith Rovers]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 = {{goal|}} {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =Cantwell {{goal|}}\n|stadium =[[Starks Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =D\n|date =27 August 1947\n|round =[[1947-48 Scottish Football League|Division B]]\n|score = 2\u20132\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[Stenhousemuir F.C.|Stenhousemuir]]\n|goals1 =Morrison {{goal|}}<br>Donegan {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =McFarlane {{goal|}}{{goal||72}}\n|stadium =[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =W Webb\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =L\n|date =20 September 1947\n|round =[[1947-48 Scottish Football League|Division B]]\n|score = 4\u20132\n|team1 =[[Leith Athletic F.C.|Leith Athletic]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Landells {{goal|11}}<Br>Broadly {{goal|28}}<Br>Roberts {{goal|53}}<br>Skinner {{goal|70}}\n|goals2 =Shields {{goal|17}}<br>Bootland {{goal|65}}\n|stadium =[[New Meadowbank]]\n|attendance =3,500\n|referee =J McDonald\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =L\n|date =27 September 1947\n|round =[[1947-48 Scottish Football League|Division B]]\n|score = 2\u20134\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]\n|goals1 =Goldie {{goal|11||74}}\n|goals2 =Brown {{goal|26||64}}<br>Goldie {{goal|35}}<br>Mayes {{goal|72}}\n|stadium =[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =2,000\n|referee =[[Jack Mowat]]\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  =L\n|date =4 October 1947\n|round =[[1947-48 Scottish Footba